title: Head Metallix 150 Squash Racquet
description:
This squash racquet has everything you're looking for - Power, Maneuverability and Control. Featuring FlexpointTM construction and MetallixTM technology, this racquet will immediately have you hitting your best shots more often. 
HEAD MetallixTM: Made of a specially designed matrix of carbon fibers and a new crystalline metal alloy. This alloys grain size is 1,000 times smaller than that of a typical metal. The decreased grain size means increased performance, or, as the Hall-Petch Effect states: smaller grains = stronger material. The result is a lighter, stronger and more powerful racquet than ever before. 

Flexpoint Technology: Breaking the rules of traditional racquet design. Consumers have long been asking for more control in a racquet, now HEAD has the answer. Flexpoint, an exciting new technology that places two precisely engineered control holes in the racquet's head. These two newly designed holes, positioned at 3 and 9 o'clock on the racquet head, work together to bring power in control. The dimple is engineered to create flexibility by reducing beam height by a maximum of 25 %. The hole increases sectional flexibility up to 50%. The racquet forms a "cup" that surrounds the ball. Dwell time is increased and control is maximized. To visualize this, think of how your hand cups a ball. This cupping effect produces control like never before, with no loss of power. The end result? Unprecedented control with absolutely no loss of power
category: Sports & Outdoors, Racquet Sports, Squash, Racquets
